248
00:20:18,957 --> 00:20:23,177
I told you. The only way to stop them
is to shoot them in the head.

249
00:20:23,369 --> 00:20:24,827
It's their only vulnerable spot.

250
00:20:25,019 --> 00:20:28,894
Don't forget it, otherwise
you'll waste time and ammunition.

251
00:20:29,086 --> 00:20:31,349
And that can prove to be fatal.

252
00:20:39,598 --> 00:20:41,286
Let's go.

253
00:20:53,027 --> 00:20:55,060
- Those were gunshots.
- They sent help.

254
00:20:55,252 --> 00:20:56,710
We're gonna get out of here.

255
00:20:56,940 --> 00:20:58,245
You should thank me.

256
00:20:58,436 --> 00:21:01,774
If you hadn't told them I was here,
they would've ignored your call.

257
00:21:02,004 --> 00:21:04,000
You might want to stick your ego
up your ass...

258
00:21:04,191 --> 00:21:07,222
...considering your own secretary
left you here to die.

259
00:21:09,486 --> 00:21:10,407
What was that?

260
00:21:10,637 --> 00:21:12,095
Someone who isn't infected.

261
00:21:12,287 --> 00:21:14,167
We have to help.

262
00:21:14,359 --> 00:21:16,277
It's too late.
There's nothing we can do.

263
00:21:16,469 --> 00:21:20,497
That's right.
I mean, if you, then I leave too.

264
00:21:20,727 --> 00:21:22,454
No, Claire, don't go.

265
00:21:22,646 --> 00:21:25,523
When my father left,
he said the same thing.

266
00:21:25,715 --> 00:21:27,787
He said he was going
to go help my mother...

267
00:21:28,017 --> 00:21:30,741
...but he didn't come back,
and neither did she.

268
00:21:30,933 --> 00:21:33,465
And if you leave,
you won't come back either.

269
00:21:33,657 --> 00:21:34,885
It's okay.

270
00:21:35,077 --> 00:21:36,765
I am gonna come back.

271
00:21:36,957 --> 00:21:40,103
- I promise.
- Really?

272
00:21:40,717 --> 00:21:44,400
By the way, do we have anything here
that can be used as a weapon?

273
00:22:08,648 --> 00:22:10,911
Never saw this coming.

274
00:22:22,498 --> 00:22:24,647
Is there anyone there?

275
00:22:30,517 --> 00:22:32,742
No answer. Never a good sign.

276
00:22:51,733 --> 00:22:53,422
Get down.

277
00:23:00,174 --> 00:23:01,709
Leon.

278
00:23:02,591 --> 00:23:05,239
- What are you doing here?
- I could ask you the same thing.

279
00:23:05,776 --> 00:23:07,579
You're the one?

280
00:23:11,032 --> 00:23:12,183
Is this it?

281
00:23:12,375 --> 00:23:14,754
- Yup.
- Reinforcements?

282
00:23:14,945 --> 00:23:16,518
None. We're getting out alone.

283
00:23:17,094 --> 00:23:21,122
Is it too much to hope
you at least have some sort of a plan?

284
00:23:21,314 --> 00:23:24,192
- We're gonna run across the lobby.
- Are you insane?

285
00:23:24,384 --> 00:23:26,225
The lobby is crawling
with those creatures.

286
00:23:26,417 --> 00:23:27,606
It's also the widest area.

287
00:23:27,798 --> 00:23:30,100
It's too dangerous
to take the long way around.

288
00:23:30,292 --> 00:23:31,251
He's right.

289
00:23:32,978 --> 00:23:35,203
They aren't fast.
We can get by them.

290
00:23:35,395 --> 00:23:36,316
Oh, yeah?

291
00:23:36,546 --> 00:23:38,272
And since when
did the NGO member...

292
00:23:38,464 --> 00:23:40,306
...become such an authority
on the subject?

293
00:23:40,498 --> 00:23:42,608
She's one of the rare survivors
of Raccoon City.

294
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:45,524
She has more experience
with this kind of hellish nightmare...

295
00:23:45,716 --> 00:23:47,557
...than anyone else here.

296
00:23:47,787 --> 00:23:49,591
Hey, Raccoon City,
isn't that where the-?

297
00:23:49,782 --> 00:23:51,202
Yes.

298
00:24:04,170 --> 00:24:05,129
Run.

299
00:24:15,411 --> 00:24:17,407
Keep up with me, Rani.

300
00:24:19,363 --> 00:24:21,780
- Go.
- Thanks.

301
00:24:28,571 --> 00:24:29,761
Senator.

302
00:24:36,628 --> 00:24:38,240
Sir.

303
00:24:47,409 --> 00:24:49,213
Greg.

304
00:24:57,730 --> 00:24:59,034
Shit.

305
00:24:59,226 --> 00:25:00,646
He got bit.

306
00:25:00,876 --> 00:25:03,063
He damn well got bit.

307
00:25:03,255 --> 00:25:04,943
Stay back.

308
00:25:06,516 --> 00:25:07,974
Go on without me.

309
00:25:08,166 --> 00:25:09,931
- Greg. Wait.
- Greg.

310
00:25:10,122 --> 00:25:11,082
You got this?

311
00:25:12,885 --> 00:25:14,228
Greg.

312
00:25:14,420 --> 00:25:17,335
Greg. No.

313
00:25:17,527 --> 00:25:19,215
Greg.

314
00:25:19,407 --> 00:25:21,748
Greg!

315
00:25:30,956 --> 00:25:32,605
You okay?

316
00:25:33,795 --> 00:25:36,442
Do I look like I'm okay?

317
00:25:45,957 --> 00:25:47,568
Are we going to make it out of here?

318
00:25:47,760 --> 00:25:50,830
We have a clear view
and a straight path to the exit.

319
00:25:55,357 --> 00:25:56,930
We'll take out as many as we can...

320
00:25:59,155 --> 00:26:00,767
...and run like hell.

321
00:26:00,958 --> 00:26:02,340
Angela, back me up.

322
00:26:04,335 --> 00:26:05,831
Got it.

323
00:26:15,001 --> 00:26:17,149
Can't you get rid of them any faster?

324
00:26:17,341 --> 00:26:19,336
They're starting to gather over here.

325
00:26:22,751 --> 00:26:24,477
We're not gonna make it out,
are we?

326
00:26:24,669 --> 00:26:25,935
It's getting tough.

327
00:26:26,127 --> 00:26:27,355
We gotta go.

328
00:26:58,624 --> 00:27:00,274
Rani.

329
00:27:20,071 --> 00:27:22,488
Claire.

330
00:27:42,093 --> 00:27:43,091
You all right?

331
00:27:43,781 --> 00:27:45,393
Barely.

332
00:27:46,697 --> 00:27:49,421
- Rani, are you okay?
- Claire.

333
00:27:52,990 --> 00:27:54,639
Let's go.

334
00:28:06,993 --> 00:28:08,643
Thank you.

335
00:28:15,319 --> 00:28:16,930
Where's the senator?

336
00:28:26,254 --> 00:28:27,443
Finally.

337
00:28:27,635 --> 00:28:29,169
I'm over here.

338
00:28:37,802 --> 00:28:40,257
The light. Run towards the light.

339
00:29:00,592 --> 00:29:02,357
Get that perimeter set up. Move.

340
00:29:02,548 --> 00:29:04,467
Don't stand there, man. Set it up.

341
00:29:07,498 --> 00:29:08,956
Move in, move in. Open fire.

342
00:29:09,148 --> 00:29:11,718
- Light them up, boys. Light them up.
- Get a move on.

343
00:29:11,910 --> 00:29:13,214
Move, move.

344
00:29:17,627 --> 00:29:19,698
Rani!

345
00:29:20,696 --> 00:29:22,422
Rani.

346
00:29:22,614 --> 00:29:24,302
Aunt.

347
00:29:27,065 --> 00:29:29,444
- Aunt.
- Oh, my God. You're all right.

348
00:29:29,635 --> 00:29:31,746
I was so scared.

349
00:29:33,856 --> 00:29:35,582
Aunt.

350
00:29:35,774 --> 00:29:36,848
Aunt.

351
00:29:37,040 --> 00:29:39,035
They were everywhere.

352
00:29:39,227 --> 00:29:42,181
- I didn't think I would see you again.
- I can't stand kids.

353
00:29:42,373 --> 00:29:44,599
They're a real pain in the ass.

354
00:29:45,903 --> 00:29:49,011
Oh, my poor darling.

355
00:29:49,740 --> 00:29:50,737
Bastard.

356
00:29:50,967 --> 00:29:52,464
That girl will have nightmares...

357
00:29:52,656 --> 00:29:54,689
...for the rest of her life
because of you.

358
00:29:54,881 --> 00:29:58,180
Let me go. Give her to me. Please.

359
00:29:58,372 --> 00:29:59,485
I got it, I got it.

360
00:29:59,677 --> 00:30:00,828
Claire.

361
00:30:01,019 --> 00:30:02,132
You okay?

362
00:30:02,362 --> 00:30:04,818
Oh, honey, I know.
But she's fine, really.

363
00:30:05,048 --> 00:30:06,391
We just have to wait.

364
00:30:41,113 --> 00:30:42,264
No problem.

365
00:30:44,220 --> 00:30:46,369
I'll take care of it.

366
00:30:52,431 --> 00:30:55,193
We can use that
in the worst-case scenario.

367
00:30:55,385 --> 00:30:57,227
I have no intention
of letting WilPharma...

368
00:30:57,419 --> 00:30:59,682
...end up looking like a savior.

369
00:31:28,304 --> 00:31:30,146
Hey, Hunnigan. I'm reporting in.

370
00:31:30,337 --> 00:31:31,488
I already heard.

371
00:31:31,719 --> 00:31:34,174
The Marines landed
in the nick of time and saved the day.

372
00:31:34,404 --> 00:31:36,092
I can't tell you how relieved I am.

373
00:31:36,284 --> 00:31:38,855
I'm amazed and impressed
you got authorization for that.

374
00:31:39,047 --> 00:31:42,730
- You must have pulled a few strings.
- Yes. Well, I have my resources.

375
00:31:43,382 --> 00:31:45,953
After I received confirmation
from USAMRIID...

376
00:31:46,144 --> 00:31:49,022
...that the virus used in this attack
was indeed the T-virus...

377
00:31:49,214 --> 00:31:51,055
...I submitted a plan
to the president.

378
00:31:51,247 --> 00:31:53,588
He pushed it through
as a special emergency act.

379
00:31:53,779 --> 00:31:56,926
Every Marine involved in the assault
was vaccinated.

380
00:31:57,117 --> 00:32:00,033
- Have the terrorists made demands?
- No, not yet.

381
00:32:00,225 --> 00:32:02,719
But the FBl captured a member
of General Grande's army...

382
00:32:02,911 --> 00:32:04,983
...in Los Angeles just moments ago.

383
00:32:05,174 --> 00:32:08,014
When we interrogate him,
he might give us some information...

384
00:32:08,205 --> 00:32:09,663
...that'll establish a link...

385
00:32:09,894 --> 00:32:12,311
...between this terrorist attack
and the one in India.

386
00:32:12,502 --> 00:32:14,498
Maybe we'll dig up a lead
on the whereabouts...

387
00:32:14,728 --> 00:32:16,608
...of former
Umbrella Corporation employees.

388
00:32:16,800 --> 00:32:19,792
They've gotta be the ones peddling
the virus on the black market.

389
00:32:20,444 --> 00:32:22,746
What the hell is going on?

390
00:32:22,938 --> 00:32:24,780
Why are WilPharma drugs
being brought here?

391
00:32:24,972 --> 00:32:26,238
It's the vaccine.

392
00:32:28,233 --> 00:32:30,420
You. What are you doing here?

393
00:32:30,957 --> 00:32:34,218
He's WilPharma's head researcher.

394
00:32:36,443 --> 00:32:39,091
May I introduce Frederic Downing.

395
00:32:39,282 --> 00:32:41,623
He's the one who developed
a vaccine for the virus...

396
00:32:41,815 --> 00:32:45,421
...which you, in particular,
are so familiar with.

397
00:32:47,224 --> 00:32:50,179
You mean the infection
in the terminal?

398
00:32:50,562 --> 00:32:55,435
You thought that was
WilPharma-engineered, didn't you?

399
00:32:57,085 --> 00:32:59,310
Utterly ridiculous.

400
00:32:59,502 --> 00:33:00,883
An inoculation.

401
00:33:01,075 --> 00:33:05,909
That's what they've been working on.
A way to prevent further outbreaks.

402
00:33:06,523 --> 00:33:09,093
- But-
- Claire, it's true.

403
00:33:10,973 --> 00:33:12,623
- You knew?
- Yes.

404
00:33:12,853 --> 00:33:15,961
I didn't think its use
would be sanctioned this quickly.

405
00:33:16,268 --> 00:33:18,647
Then the human testing
that took place in India...

406
00:33:18,839 --> 00:33:21,678
An attack by terrorists
that somehow got hold of the T-virus.

407
00:33:21,870 --> 00:33:24,402
All the members of the group
supported by General Grande...

408
00:33:24,632 --> 00:33:26,819
...were infected,
so we don't know the details.

409
00:33:27,011 --> 00:33:30,003
The U.S. government obtained
permission from Indian authorities...

410
00:33:30,195 --> 00:33:34,185
...to administer the T-virus vaccine
to the nearby communities.

411
00:33:34,377 --> 00:33:37,830
A vaccine secretly developed
by WilPharma.

412
00:33:38,022 --> 00:33:39,173
It was a success.

413
00:33:39,365 --> 00:33:42,166
The infection rate
was kept as minimal as possible.

414
00:33:42,357 --> 00:33:45,427
Why the hell didn't you
break out the vaccine for this?

415
00:33:45,657 --> 00:33:48,611
If we'd been inoculated before
we entered the terminal, Greg would-

416
00:33:48,803 --> 00:33:50,875
Inoculation would have been
entirely possible...

417
00:33:51,067 --> 00:33:53,752
...had Terra-Save not backed us
into an adversarial corner.

418
00:33:56,860 --> 00:33:58,970
Had we been able
to follow proper procedure...

419
00:33:59,162 --> 00:34:02,615
...as outlined in the original schedule,
the government medical stockpile...

420
00:34:02,807 --> 00:34:06,068
...could have been shipped anywhere
in the U.S. within 12 hours.

421
00:34:06,260 --> 00:34:09,061
Oh, my God. Then...

422
00:34:09,253 --> 00:34:11,248
...it's all our fault.

423
00:34:13,243 --> 00:34:16,044
I wouldn't argue with you there.

424
00:34:22,029 --> 00:34:24,868
We just ended up
making things worse.

425
00:34:25,060 --> 00:34:26,710
That's not true.

426
00:34:26,901 --> 00:34:29,625
The villains here
are the ones who used the virus.

427
00:34:29,856 --> 00:34:32,580
But worse than them
are the ones who made it.

428
00:34:32,771 --> 00:34:36,570
Seven years ago,
our lives were changed forever...

429
00:34:36,762 --> 00:34:39,371
...by the virus from Umbrella Corp.

430
00:34:46,890 --> 00:34:49,001
Umbrella collapsed...

431
00:34:52,415 --> 00:34:55,907
...but their viral legacy
continues to spread.

432
00:34:57,787 --> 00:35:00,664
I'm gonna scrub this virus
from the face of the Earth.

433
00:35:04,769 --> 00:35:08,414
You chose the role of rescuer
rather than fighter, like me.

434
00:35:08,606 --> 00:35:12,174
You chose a path that
your brother and I couldn't follow.

435
00:35:12,366 --> 00:35:14,438
You weren't wrong.

436
00:35:15,934 --> 00:35:18,198
Leon, thank you.

437
00:35:29,900 --> 00:35:31,626
Hurry.

438
00:35:34,235 --> 00:35:36,153
Find some extinguishers.

439
00:35:36,345 --> 00:35:38,225
Clear the area
before the gas tanks blow.

440
00:35:38,417 --> 00:35:39,415
Let's go, let's go.

441
00:35:39,606 --> 00:35:41,908
Where's the rest of the team?
Come on.

442
00:35:42,100 --> 00:35:43,942
- How do I use this thing?
- Help.

443
00:35:44,134 --> 00:35:45,745
Somebody help. I'm stuck.

444
00:35:45,937 --> 00:35:47,510
I'm coming, I'm coming.

445
00:35:47,702 --> 00:35:49,812
Hurry up, come on.

446
00:35:59,634 --> 00:36:02,243
- What happened?
- The trucks carrying the vaccine-

447
00:36:02,435 --> 00:36:04,353
How much vaccine is left?

448
00:36:04,583 --> 00:36:07,653
Everything we brought today was all
we were able to scrape together...

449
00:36:07,844 --> 00:36:10,031
...from vaccine samples
inside the company.

450
00:36:10,223 --> 00:36:12,372
And most of that has just been lost.

451
00:36:12,563 --> 00:36:13,945
Where's the manufacturing data?

452
00:36:14,137 --> 00:36:17,167
- You think they're after the data too?
- Could it be?

453
00:36:17,359 --> 00:36:20,429
Why don't you tell us
what their demands are already?

454
00:36:21,963 --> 00:36:25,378
If you don't wanna talk
I'll just go directly to the president.

455
00:36:25,570 --> 00:36:27,488
The truth.

456
00:36:28,140 --> 00:36:29,330
Truth?

457
00:36:29,522 --> 00:36:30,903
They demand the truth.

458
00:36:31,095 --> 00:36:34,471
The viral weapon from which Umbrella
Corporation's T-virus was derived.

459
00:36:34,663 --> 00:36:38,384
They wanna reveal everyone from the
U.S. government who was involved.

460
00:36:38,576 --> 00:36:40,725
Was the government
really involved?

461
00:36:40,917 --> 00:36:42,873
The proof went up in smoke
with Raccoon City.

462
00:36:43,065 --> 00:36:45,252
Wait a minute.
The truth didn't disappear.

463
00:36:45,444 --> 00:36:47,899
- There never was any.
- Convince the terrorists of that.

464
00:36:48,091 --> 00:36:50,815
If they don't get that information,
what will happen?

465
00:36:51,007 --> 00:36:53,961
They'll disperse the T-virus
in every populated area in the U.S.

466
00:36:54,191 --> 00:36:55,342
The deadline is midnight.

467
00:36:55,534 --> 00:36:57,031
That's only four hours from now.

468
00:36:57,261 --> 00:36:58,872
And there's no vaccine left.

469
00:36:59,064 --> 00:37:01,021
Can we find out
who the terrorists are?

470
00:37:01,213 --> 00:37:04,397
I have a clue as to the identity
of one of them.

471
00:37:04,589 --> 00:37:07,850
Right after the first infected victims
appeared in the airport terminal...

472
00:37:08,042 --> 00:37:11,572
...I noticed a man in the lobby.
His name is Curtis Miller.

473
00:37:11,763 --> 00:37:14,027
I know him.
He's one of those bleeding hearts...

474
00:37:14,219 --> 00:37:16,828
...protesting the construction
of the new research facility.

475
00:37:17,020 --> 00:37:19,629
If the terrorists' demands
are the release of information...

476
00:37:19,859 --> 00:37:21,969
...on what really happened
in Raccoon City...

477
00:37:22,199 --> 00:37:24,962
- ... then he might-
- It can't be.

478
00:37:28,760 --> 00:37:30,064
Curtis Miller is...

479
00:37:31,983 --> 00:37:33,978
...my older brother.

480
00:38:17,754 --> 00:38:20,095
My brother
wouldn't do something like this.

481
00:38:20,287 --> 00:38:22,205
He was arrested
for threatening WilPharma.

482
00:38:22,397 --> 00:38:24,353
He just demanded
information be made public.

483
00:38:24,545 --> 00:38:28,574
Unfortunately, the rest of the world
doesn't see it that way.

484
00:38:29,533 --> 00:38:31,873
If you claim he's not a terrorist...

485
00:38:32,065 --> 00:38:35,902
...why don't you bring him here
to explain himself? Now.

486
00:39:03,679 --> 00:39:07,209
You're sure packing a lot of hardware
just to go see your brother.

487
00:39:15,228 --> 00:39:16,839
Where are you going?

488
00:39:17,031 --> 00:39:19,563
I'm going to the office
and check on the development data.

489
00:39:19,755 --> 00:39:24,282
Can I help you with something?
Don't worry. I'm not scheming...

490
00:39:24,474 --> 00:39:28,042
...to infiltrate your organization
for my own devious purposes.

491
00:39:28,234 --> 00:39:31,342
I'm afraid there's only one thing
you can do.

492
00:39:32,032 --> 00:39:34,987
Join me for a late afternoon tea.

493
00:39:39,974 --> 00:39:45,192
There you are. Comfortable?
It'll be nice to have some company.

494
00:40:18,418 --> 00:40:20,835
This is the road to Curtis' home.

495
00:41:19,766 --> 00:41:23,143
I haven't heard a word from Curtis
in three years.

496
00:41:25,061 --> 00:41:29,051
He lost his wife and child
in the Raccoon City tragedy.

497
00:42:02,814 --> 00:42:04,886
That's odd. It won't accept my card.

498
00:42:05,116 --> 00:42:07,725
- Has that happened before?
- No. This is the first time.

499
00:42:09,068 --> 00:42:11,331
I'll have to use the master code.

500
00:43:08,076 --> 00:43:10,685
We're entering an air dome.

501
00:43:13,447 --> 00:43:14,483
The roof is supported...

502
00:43:14,675 --> 00:43:19,547
...by creating a difference between
the exterior and interior air pressure.

